<i>Killing doubters, killing haters.</i>

2279
02:07:23,762 --> 02:07:27,057
- Bring it in. Bring it in.
- Some motherfucking money, right?

2280
02:07:27,140 --> 02:07:28,368
And a personal one to you, bro.

2281
02:07:28,392 --> 02:07:30,519
<i>You just celebrated
your 36th birthday.</i>

2282
02:07:30,602 --> 02:07:32,521
<i>Everyone out there is saying,
"He's too old..."</i>

2283
02:07:32,604 --> 02:07:34,314
That's some strong shit. Oh!

2284
02:07:34,648 --> 02:07:37,567
That's my nigga right there, boy.
Look at that motherfucker, man.

2285
02:07:37,651 --> 02:07:39,569
I know that man. I know that man.

2286
02:07:39,653 --> 02:07:42,030
My dad's good with him!

2287
02:07:42,781 --> 02:07:44,324
Hey! I can't think.

2288
02:07:44,408 --> 02:07:48,287
Amy, he was naked and drunk, okay?
I'm calling the police.

2289
02:07:48,412 --> 02:07:50,956
<i>All the dues and everything
that I put into this,</i>

2290
02:07:51,039 --> 02:07:53,625
<i>you didn't think that
I would show up to game seven?</i>

2291
02:07:53,709 --> 02:07:54,710
<i>That's a joke.</i>

2292
02:07:54,835 --> 02:07:57,337
<i>Paul Pierce bows out
of this one. He goes to the bench.</i>

2293
02:07:57,421 --> 02:07:59,840
<i>Did you feel that he needed
to shoulder his burden...</i>

2294
02:07:59,923 --> 02:08:02,509
- It's all there.
- Thank you so much.

2295
02:08:04,761 --> 02:08:06,888
<i>...for us to come out
and carry that burden.</i>

2296
02:08:06,972 --> 02:08:10,392
<i>He does a lot for our team.
It's not just down to one guy.</i>

2297
02:08:10,475 --> 02:08:13,603
<i>We all shared that responsibility
and did a good job.</i>

2298
02:08:15,063 --> 02:08:19,067
<i>But in the end, I felt like it was just me
and the rock, nothing else.</i>

2299
02:08:19,151 --> 02:08:21,695
<i>Is this the end
of the Big Three as we know it?</i>

2300
02:08:21,778 --> 02:08:25,490
<i>No, I wouldn't say that.
I think we have a lot more in our tank.</i>

2301
02:08:25,574 --> 02:08:27,367
<i>We have a lot more to prove.</i>

2302
02:08:27,451 --> 02:08:29,745
<i>We want to win.
We're trying to get another ring.</i>

2303
02:08:29,828 --> 02:08:32,748
Oh, my God. Wayne, thank you so much.

2304
02:08:32,831 --> 02:08:35,125
My pleasure. A lot of money.

2305
02:08:35,208 --> 02:08:37,627
- Come to the Avalon. Have one drink.
- No, I can't.

2306
02:08:37,711 --> 02:08:39,880
- I don't want to twist your arm.
- I gotta go, baby.

2307
02:08:39,963 --> 02:08:42,174
- Just have one drink.
- We can go now.

2308
02:08:43,800 --> 02:08:46,219
<i>In the end,
it's all about winning, nothing else.</i>

2309
02:08:46,303 --> 02:08:47,929
<i>Man, I feel great.</i>

2310
02:08:48,055 --> 02:08:50,140
Go, go! Burn that fucking camera!

2311
02:08:50,932 --> 02:08:53,685
- All right, go, go! Go, go!
- Okay, I got it. I got it.

2312
02:08:54,770 --> 02:08:56,605
Nico, I can't find the camera.

2313
02:08:56,688 --> 02:08:58,732
And make sure you get
all those electronics.

2314
02:08:58,815 --> 02:09:02,152
Anything that videotapes,
put it in the fucking bag!

2315
02:09:04,154 --> 02:09:06,365
<i>...the Big Three, Paul Pierce...</i>


